{"type":"npc_class","name":"SUPPORT","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/npc_class.svg","system":{"lid":"npcc_support","name":"SUPPORT","role":"support","info":{"flavor":"Support-archetype mechs keep their allies alive and operational with a broad library of immediate triage systems, from basic flash-weld plating through to shallow–medium structural reinforcement packs and whitewash nanite slurry. From the famed Laughter of a Solemn God, working the front lines of Boundary Garden’s battlefields, to the precision actions undertaken by the rogue-world hunters of ExtraSolar Acquisitions, Inc., the efficacy of Support-archetype mechs is unparalleled when mech teams need to stay alive longer than deployment.","tactics":"Supports are bulky mechs that can’t deal any damage but have access to powerful healing and condition-clearing effects. Despite their resilience, they have no way to defend themselves and need to get close to their allies in order to be effective. Savvy players will shoot and destroy their Restock Drones before they are activated, denying an opportunity for healing."},"power":100,"base_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_sealant_gun_support","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_restock_drone_support","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_nano_repair_cloud_support","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"optional_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_remote_reboot_support","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_empowered_cloud_support","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_remote_cloud_support","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_defensive_pulse_support","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_latch_drone_support","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"base_stats":{"activations":[1,1,1],"armor":[1,1,1],"hp":[15,18,22],"evade":[8,10,12],"edef":[8,10,12],"heatcap":[8,8,8],"speed":[4,4,4],"sensor":[10,10,10],"save":[10,12,14],"hull":[1,1,1],"agility":[-2,-1,-1],"systems":[0,1,2],"engineering":[2,4,6],"size":[[2],[2],[2]]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"kpZ1DNCgd1F5Mepo":3},"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"lancer","systemVersion":"1.6.1","coreVersion":"10.303","createdTime":1690825120550,"modifiedTime":1690825120550,"lastModifiedBy":"kpZ1DNCgd1F5Mepo"},"_id":"Wi4aNwTuE61Lk9b0"}
{"type":"npc_class","name":"ENGINEER","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/npc_class.svg","system":{"lid":"npcc_engineer","name":"ENGINEER","role":"striker","info":{"flavor":"Various types of localized Engineer-class mechs are common throughout the galaxy, unique to the worlds or theaters in which they operate. The Engineer has long existed as an archetype, but it remained largely undefined until a full design doctrine was laid out by Corrida Isolde-Nollet, an Armory civil service director on Ras Shamra. In all cases, the mission of Engineers is the same: defend, maintain, secure. Engineers operate best in the middle or rear of the battle line, coordinating the defense of important positions and overseeing comprehensive deployment of all operational assets. Remember: if you can’t get to the enemy, you lose.","tactics":"Engineers’ Deployable Turrets make them potent force multipliers, as they can deploy one every turn. If enemies don’t deal with an Engineer's turrets quickly, their potential damage quickly skyrockets – even more when they target characters with Engineer’s Mark. Without Engineer’s Mark, turrets attack the nearest target, which players can use to control who takes damage."},"power":100,"base_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_flak_cannon_engineer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_deployable_turret_engineer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_engineers_mark_engineer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"optional_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_power_deployer_engineer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_skyshield_protocol_engineer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_shepherd_field_engineer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_mobile_turrets_engineer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_arsenal_engineer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"base_stats":{"activations":[1,1,1],"armor":[0,0,0],"hp":[20,20,20],"evade":[7,9,11],"edef":[10,10,12],"heatcap":[10,12,14],"speed":[3,3,3],"sensor":[15,15,15],"save":[10,12,14],"hull":[-1,-1,-1],"agility":[-1,-1,-1],"systems":[1,2,3],"engineering":[3,4,6],"size":[[1],[1],[1]]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"kpZ1DNCgd1F5Mepo":3},"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"lancer","systemVersion":"1.6.1","coreVersion":"10.303","createdTime":1690825120480,"modifiedTime":1690825120480,"lastModifiedBy":"kpZ1DNCgd1F5Mepo"},"_id":"XC6VU97IzcOsn95v"}
{"type":"npc_class","name":"RONIN","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/npc_class.svg","system":{"lid":"npcc_ronin","name":"RONIN","role":"striker","info":{"flavor":"Ronin frames differ from those favored by Berserkers and Demolishers in that they aren’t retrofitted or improvised for creative tactical applications – they are purpose-built to excel in melee combat by boutique fabricators. Although they are seen as somewhat antique by many commentators, the rise of stasis- and mag-based defensive technologies has made Ronins more viable in modern combat.<br>Ronin are common among both martial cultures and performance-combat firms, where their superb melee abilities elevate them above the competition. They see less use in cultures that have a preference for ranged combat, but there is a certain prestige accorded to pilots who adopt ancient weapons and survive to do it again. The mythic lancer Susanoo elevated this archetype to legendary status when she endorsed the GRAMtech Strike-1 chassis, which she piloted alongside numerous Albatross wings during the Neo-Celestine Disappointment.","tactics":"Ronins are no-nonsense, high-damage melee strikers. Rebound makes it dangerous for enemies to attack Ronins with ranged weapons, but they tend to suffer against armored enemies and are heavily reliant on Accuracy."},"power":100,"base_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_carbon_fiber_sword_ronin","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_rebound_ronin","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"optional_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_charged_slash_ronin","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_chaff_launchers_ronin","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_echo_edge_ronin","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_instinct_mode_ronin","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_extended_blade_ronin","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"base_stats":{"activations":[1,1,1],"armor":[0,0,0],"hp":[18,20,22],"evade":[10,13,16],"edef":[7,7,7],"heatcap":[7,7,7],"speed":[5,5,6],"sensor":[10,10,10],"save":[10,13,15],"hull":[1,2,4],"agility":[2,4,5],"systems":[-1,-1,-1],"engineering":[-1,-1,-1],"size":[[1],[1],[1]]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"kpZ1DNCgd1F5Mepo":3},"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"lancer","systemVersion":"1.6.1","coreVersion":"10.303","createdTime":1690825120517,"modifiedTime":1690825120517,"lastModifiedBy":"kpZ1DNCgd1F5Mepo"},"_id":"b0A06EsiSLuTMPND"}
{"type":"npc_class","name":"DEMOLISHER","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/npc_class.svg","system":{"lid":"npcc_demolisher","name":"DEMOLISHER","role":"defender","info":{"flavor":"The lengthy siege of Jadigmora City saw the development of the first true Demolisher frames. Based on antique Berserker mechs, Demolishers swapped dramatic heat flows for more sustainable systems, improved hydraulic strength, and stabilizers for supermassive melee weapons. Demolisher pilots soon discovered a range of new applications for their concussion-wave ordnance. A lancer named Hayes Rothford and their NHP, Clarke, were the first pilot/co-pilot team to truly show the power of the platform, singlehandedly bringing down a siege frigate in low orbit.","tactics":"Demolishers are slow, resilient defenders that dish out plenty of damage and stuns when they get close to the enemy. Use their size and power in melee combat to force enemy characters to move away instead of fighting them, and Dig In to shrug off heavy hits."},"power":100,"base_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_demolition_hammer_demolisher","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_dig_in_demolisher","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_shock_armor_demolisher","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_heavy_frame_demolisher","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"optional_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_broad_sweep_haft_demolisher","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_kinetic_compensation_demolisher","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_concussion_missiles_demolisher","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_seismic_destroyer_demolisher","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_sap_demolisher","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"base_stats":{"activati