{"type":"npc_class","name":"HUMAN","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/npc_class.svg","system":{"lid":"npcc_human","name":"HUMAN","role":"biological","info":{"flavor":"All kinds of people end up on the battlefield, including pilots, VIPs, and bystanders.<br>You will mostly use Human NPCs when someone climbs out of their mech mid-battle; if you want a proper group of infantry, use the Squad class instead. Humans can never take other templates, and cannot gain structure.","tactics":""},"power":100,"base_features":[],"optional_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_ranged_weapon_human","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_melee_weapon_human","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_anti_armor_weapon_human","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_veteran_human","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_armored_human","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_armored_human_2","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"base_stats":{"activations":[1,1,1],"armor":[0,0,0],"hp":[6,6,6],"evade":[10,10,10],"edef":[10,10,10],"heatcap":[0,0,0],"speed":[4,4,4],"sensor":[5,5,5],"save":[10,10,10],"hull":[1,2,3],"agility":[1,2,3],"systems":[1,2,3],"engineering":[1,2,3],"size":[[0.5],[0.5],[0.5]]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"kpZ1DNCgd1F5Mepo":3},"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"lancer","systemVersion":"1.6.1","coreVersion":"10.303","createdTime":1690825120559,"modifiedTime":1690825120559,"lastModifiedBy":"kpZ1DNCgd1F5Mepo"},"_id":"glY6XnjxXeW9obbS"}
{"type":"npc_class","name":"ARCHER","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/npc_class.svg","system":{"lid":"npcc_archer","name":"ARCHER","role":"controller","info":{"flavor":"The basis of the Archer archetype, Ursa Major’s Gatekeeper Key-II, was popularized by Ichabod Carden’s heroic actions in the Battle of Terramoto. Archer-archetype mechs sacrifice armor for powerful targeting and superpositional maneuvering systems, making them especially popular with pilots who prefer to have control over the precise destination of each shot.","tactics":"Archers excel at inflicting “choice punishment” on their enemies – they make characters choose between taking certain actions or letting the Archer attack them. Use Archers to lock down mobile or hard-hitting PCs or to cover for more vulnerable allies. Keep in mind that Archers are most effective when they can get fairly close to their targets, but they aren’t especially durable."},"power":100,"base_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_light_machine_gun_archer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_suppress_archer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_moving_target_archer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_superior_sentinel_archer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"optional_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_blinding_shells_archer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_impending_threat_archer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_covering_fire_archer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_rapid_response_archer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_hail_of_fire_archer","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"base_stats":{"activations":[1,1,1],"armor":[0,0,1],"hp":[16,20,20],"evade":[8,10,12],"edef":[8,10,12],"heatcap":[8,8,8],"speed":[5,5,6],"sensor":[15,15,15],"save":[11,13,16],"hull":[-1,-1,-1],"agility":[2,3,4],"systems":[2,3,4],"engineering":[-1,-1,-1],"size":[[1],[1],[1]]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"kpZ1DNCgd1F5Mepo":3},"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"lancer","systemVersion":"1.6.1","coreVersion":"10.303","createdTime":1690825120438,"modifiedTime":1690825120438,"lastModifiedBy":"kpZ1DNCgd1F5Mepo"},"_id":"hDudYYrEJM8KsJfK"}
{"type":"npc_class","name":"SENTINEL","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/npc_class.svg","system":{"lid":"npcc_sentinel","name":"SENTINEL","role":"defender","info":{"flavor":"Sentinel archetypes are typically employed as guards and escorts, often in the retinues of commanders or posted in defense of artillery. These mechs and their pilots employ advanced suites of technology to ensure their wards stay alive and operational, even if that costs their own chassis – or lives. Unlike the heavier Bastion archetypes, Sentinels are quick and light: they practice active defense, preemptively striking with suites of advanced technical, systemic, and direct weaponry to protect their charges.","tactics":"Sentinels are fast defenders that focus on protecting their allies with Overwatch. They are fairly short-range attackers, relying on positioning to get the most from their kit, and aren’t as resilient as other defenders."},"power":100,"base_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_combat_shotgun_sentinel","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_retractable_sword_sentinel","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_eye_of_midnight_sentinel","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_guardian_sentinel","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"optional_features":[{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_punisher_ammunition_sentinel","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_wrath_lock_sentinel","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_impaler_sentinel","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_rapid_response_sentinel","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_bodyguard_sentinel","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"},{"id":"","fallback_lid":"npcf_reflexive_blow_sentinel","type":"npc_feature","reg_name":"comp_core"}],"base_stats":{"activations":[1,1,1],"